						<summary>

						<p>This is also in Vaṭṭeḻuttu script and is assignable to <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I.</hi> It records a gift of 31 sheep for a perpetual lamp in the temple of Tiruvēṅgaḍanilai-Perumānaḍigaḷ at Tiruttaṅgāl a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> village by Dēvaguḍi Kālaṉ Ālaiyaṉ <hi rend="bold">Koṟṟaṉ-Kiḻavaṉ of Kāḍānūr</hi> in Malli-nāḍu agreed to maintain the gift. </p>						

						</summary>
